{
  "text": "Although the AGM model has quickly acquired the status of standard model of theory change, several researchers (for an overview see [CITATION_1] ) have pointed out its inadequateness in several contexts and proposed several extensions and generalizations to that framework. One of the most relevant of the proposed extensions of the AGM model of contraction is to use sets of sentences not (necessarily) closed under logical consequence -which are designated belief bases -rather than belief sets to represent belief states.",
  "citation_candidates": [
